This example exercises the SecureTCPSocket and friends.

Use ./mkcerts-rsa (or ./mkcerts-dsa) to create certificates for both client and server.
NOTE: If you're running on Windows and don't have localhost in your
hosts file, edit client/bin/client.xml and replace localhost with 127.0.0.1.

To build the server:

build -o:thekogans -p:stream -e:securetcpecho_server -c:$config -t:$type

To build the client:

build -o:thekogans -p:stream -e:securetcpecho_client -c:$config -t:$type

To run the server, open a command prompt.

If you're using the Flat naming convention, navigate to server/bin and type:

thekogans_stream_securetcpecho_server-$TOOLCHAIN_TRIPLET-$config-$type.$version$TOOLCHAIN_PROGRAM_SUFFIX -c -l:Debug server.xml

To run the client, open a command prompt, navigate to client/bin and type:

Windows:
ipconfig

Linux/OS X:
ifconfig

./thekogans_stream_securetcpecho_client-$TOOLCHAIN_TRIPLET-$config-$type.$version$TOOLCHAIN_PROGRAM_SUFFIX -l:Debug client.xml

If you're using the Hierarchical naming convention, navigate to server/bin/$TOOLCHAIN_BRANCH/$config/$type and type:

thekogans_stream_securetcpecho_server.$version$TOOLCHAIN_PROGRAM_SUFFIX -c -l:Debug server.xml

To run the client, open a command prompt, navigate to client/bin/$TOOLCHAIN_BRANCH/$config/$type and type:

Windows:
ipconfig

Linux/OS X:
ifconfig

./thekogans_stream_securetcpecho_client.$version$TOOLCHAIN_PROGRAM_SUFFIX -l:Debug client.xml
